g.text: After Processing: partial output or 100% output available. }

text.tspan: getOutputLocation could be called earlier. Data Storage also can be performed periodically at any time prior to notifyDataAvailable().
notifyState(State.COMPLETED) must be used by the Application to inform the Host when processing is 100% completed. The Host
must act upon this notification to save data prior to setting the state back to IDLE.
Since notifyDataAvailable() is sent from the application to the Host periodically, the Host is aware of all data available to be saved
prior to the application setting the state to COMPLETED. An application need not track this data further, (e.g., need not be able to
create files with the data) as soon as it receives setState(State.IDLE) from the Host.
Host submits data from OutputDir to DICOM repository, GRID repository, etc.
